Package ohos.location

Class GeoConvert

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.location.GeoConvert

  • public final class GeoConvert
extends Object
    Implements mutual conversion between geographic location and address information.

    This class allows your application to convert the longitude and latitude of a location to the address information or contrariwise. The conversion result is carried in an address list, which includes information such as the longitude and latitude, city name, country code, and administrative region name.

    The conversion function is implemented by the backend service. Your application will receive an empty address list if the backend service does not support this function or return the conversion result.

    You can use the isGeoAvailable() method to check whether the backend service supports the conversion function.

    Since:

      • getAddressFromLocation

        public List<GeoAddress> getAddressFromLocation​(double latitude,
                                               double longitude,
                                               int maxItems)
                                        throws IOException
        Obtains the possible address list based on the specified longitude and latitude coordinates.

        The language of returned address descriptions is determined by the Locale object in GeoConvert.

        The number of items on the address list is subject to the actual address information returned by the backend service but will not exceed the limit you specified.

        Parameters:
        latitude - Specifies the latitude. The value range is [-90,90], in unit of degrees.
        longitude - Specifies the longitude. The value range is [-180,180], in unit of degrees.
        maxItems - Specifies the maximum length of the returned address list. The recommended value range is 1-5. The default value 1 will be used if the specified value is smaller than 1.
        Returns:
        Returns an address list. An empty address list indicates that no matching result.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the latitude is not within the range [-90,90] or the longitude is not within the range [-180,180].
        IOException - Throws this exception if the network is unavailable or an I/O exception occurs.
        Since:
        1
        See Also:
        GeoAddress

      • getAddressFromLocationName

        public List<GeoAddress> getAddressFromLocationName​(String description,
                                                   int maxItems)
                                            throws IOException
        Obtains the possible address list based on the specified location information.

        For example, the location information can be Beijing, Beijing Capital International Airport, etc.

        The language of returned address descriptions is determined by the Locale object in GeoConvert.

        The number of items on the address list is subject to the actual address information returned by the backend service but will not exceed the limit you specified.

        Parameters:
        description - Specifies the location information.
        maxItems - Specifies the maximum length of the returned address list. The recommended value range is 1-5. The default value 1 will be used if the specified value is smaller than 1.
        Returns:
        Returns an address list. An empty address list indicates that no matching result.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if description is null.
        IOException - Throws this exception if the network is unavailable or an I/O exception occurs.
        Since:

      • getAddressFromLocationName

        public List<GeoAddress> getAddressFromLocationName​(String description,
                                                   double minLatitude,
                                                   double minLongitude,
                                                   double maxLatitude,
                                                   double maxLongitude,
                                                   int maxItems)
                                            throws IOException
        Obtains the possible address list based on the specified location information and geographic region.

        You can specify a geographic region to distinguish geographic locations with the same name. This can improve the accuracy of the returned address list.

        The language of returned address descriptions is determined by the Locale object in GeoConvert.

        The number of items on the address list is subject to the actual address information returned by the backend service but will not exceed the limit you specified.

        Parameters:
        description - Specifies the location information.
        minLatitude - Indicates the minimum latitude of a rectangular area. The value range is [-90, 90].
        minLongitude - Indicates the minimum longitude of a rectangular area. The value range is [-180, 180].
        maxLatitude - Indicates the maximum latitude of a rectangular area. The value range is [-90, 90].
        maxLongitude - Indicates the maximum longitude of a rectangular area. The value range is [-180, 180].
        maxItems - Specifies the maximum length of the returned address list. The recommended value range is 1-5. The default value 1 will be used if the specified value is smaller than 1.
        Returns:
        Returns an address list. An empty address list indicates that no matching result.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if description is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the boundary latitude of the rectangular area is not within the range [-90,90].
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the boundary longitude of the rectangular area is not within the range [-180,180].
        IOException - Throws this exception if the network is unavailable or an I/O exception occurs.
        Since:
        1
        See Also:
        GeoAddress
